The paper focuses on designing person re-identification systems for real-world applications, which is a topic within computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the temporal aspect of re-identification, which involves tracking individuals over time, and this is a topic within multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the performance characteristics of different algorithms, which is a topic within cryptography and security (cs.CR), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
